The Telegraph - Calcutta : Metro

 Metro Recommends

 THE DVD

 (Landmark, Rs 595)This Radiohead performance dates back 

 to 1994, when the British band was on the verge of releasing 

 its second album, Bends. Music performed includes tracks 

 from both albums such as Creep and The Bends. 

 THE PLAY

 (Tollygunge Club, 6.30 pm, April 30) Presented by the British 

 Council, the production comprising Indian and Sri Lankan 

 actors is directed by Tim Supple. The multi-lingual venture 

 features nine languages and several Indian martial art forms.

 THE DISPLAY

 (CIMA 

 Gallery, 2 pm-7 pm; from 3 pm on Mondays; Sundays closed, 

 till May 20) The exhibition features the works of four artists 

 from Kala Bhavan, Santiniketan ? Sumitro Basak, Kingshuk Sarkar, 

 Reshmi Sarkar and Shreyashi Chatterjee. 




